{
  "texts": [
    "The program was then analyzed with user-provided function names (e.g., lock/unlock function names) to identify inconsistencies between the comments and the code.",
    "TCOMMENT [472] focuses on parameter values in Java comments and verifies the consistency of exceptions thrown under those values with the actual types of exceptions thrown by the code.",
    "Wen et al. [473] performed data mining on 1500 software code submissions and manually analyzed 500 to classify inconsistencies between code and comments.",
    "They also discussed the degree to which a code submission necessitates concurrent modification of comments, guiding for identifying and resolving inconsistencies between code and comments.",
    "Pandita et al. [474] employed machine learning models to filter out sentences in documents that describe API usage timing."
  ]
}